<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 9:05AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A LINE OF SHOWERS WITH GUSTY WINDs WILL AFFECT
STOKES...ROCKINGHAM...HENRY AND PATRICK COUNTIES AND THE CITY OF
MARTINSVILLE...
At 904 AM EDT, radar indicated showers were located along a line
extending from near Critz to near Walnut Cove. Movement was east at
35 mph.
Wind gusts up to 50 mph are possible with these showers.
Locations impacted include...
Eden...
Reidsville...
Martinsville...
Wentworth...
Mayodan...
Madison...
and Walnut Cove.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
